cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques to improve the quality of images captured by smartphone cameras. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of natural hand tremor to capture a burst of raw frames, which can be considered as a form of motion capture, making cs.GR (Graphics) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of a burst photography pipeline, which involves the processing of multiple frames, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. The paper also involves the use of signal processing techniques to improve the signal-to-noise ratio, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to align and merge the frames, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category.
